718896f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - Lispenard Street
718896f-a.text:
Church Street, west side, north from Lispenard (left) to Canal Streets, showing at that location the new Post Office site under clearance. Across same, at the right, apoear buildings, on the north side of Canal Street, at Wooster Street (center). View No. 1 shows an early Stage, while No. 2 is slightly later.
Narch 11, 1938.
View 2:  April 23, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

718894f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - Lispenard Street
718894f-a.text:
Church Street (left), at tne N. E. corner of Lispenard Street (right), showing a dining car, where formerly stood two 3--story buildings bearing No. 323. To the left is a 4 story structure No. 325. A gas station occupies the remaining frontage extending to Canal Street. The loft buildings to the right, are on the north side of Lispenard Street and
continue to Broadway.
July 12, 1939
P. L. Sperr
